  "prompt": "How do I raise berries in Pokemon Sun / Moon?",
  "response": "Raising berries in Pokemon Sun and Moon is a simple but time-consuming process. Here's a breakdown of how to do it:\n\n**1. Finding Berry Trees:**\n\n*   **Locations:** Berry trees are scattered throughout the Alola region. They appear as small mounds with leaves and sometimes already have a berry on them.  Some common locations include:\n    *   **Route 2** (Several)\n    *   **Route 3**\n    *   **Route 4**\n    *   **Route 5**\n    *   **Route 8**\n    *   **Route 10**\n    *   **Route 16**\n    *   **Ula'ula Meadow**\n    *   **Poni Wilds**\n*   **Checking Regularly:** You need to check these trees regularly (at least once a day in real-time). They will eventually regrow with berries ready to be picked.\n\n**2. Planting Berries:**\n\n*   **Harvest Berries First:** Before you can plant, you need to **harvest berries** from these trees.  Just interact with the tree when it has berries.\n*   **Berry Piles:** After harvesting, some trees will leave behind berry piles.\n*   **Planting Process:**\n    *   **Interact with the Pile:** Walk up to the berry pile and interact with it.\n    *   **Select a Berry:** Choose the berry you want to plant from your bag.\n    *   **Confirm Planting:** Confirm that you want to plant the berry.\n*   **No Limit:** You can plant as many berries as you have available in your bag.\n\n**3. Caring for Your Berry Plants:**\n\n*   **Watering:** The most important thing is to **water your plants**.  You'll see the soil around the plant looking dry if it needs watering. Interact with the plant to water it.\n*   **Time:** Berries take time to grow. Different berries have different growth times.  You'll see the plant progress through stages:\n    *   Sprout (small seedling)\n    *   Flowering\n    *   Budding\n    *   Ripening (ready to harvest)\n*   **Harvesting:** When the plant is fully grown and covered in berries, interact with it to harvest. You will collect multiple of the planted berry.\n\n**Tips for Efficient Berry Growing:**\n\n*   **Check Often:** The more often you check your berry piles, the sooner you can water them, and the faster they'll grow.\n*   **Experiment:** Different berries have different effects. Try planting various types to see which ones are most useful to you.\n*   **Berries for Stats:** Many berries can be used to reduce the effort value(EV) of a Pok\u00e9mon if you made a mistake when training them. Pomeg, Kelpsy, Qualot, Hondew, Grepa, and Tamato Berries reduce the base stat of a Pok\u00e9mon by 10 if that stat is above 100.\n*   **Held Items:** Some berries are useful held items to recover HP or cure status ailments during battle.\n\n**Key Things to Remember:**\n\n*   **Real-Time:** Berry growth is based on real-time passing.\n*   **Watering is Critical:** Neglecting watering will significantly slow down growth.\n*   **Patience:** Growing berries takes time, so be patient and check regularly.\n\nBy following these steps and being consistent with watering, you'll be able to cultivate a thriving berry garden in Pokemon Sun and Moon!  Good luck!\n",
